FLOW_PROMPTS: dict[str, str] = {
    "session_preview": "Generate a short preview with intrigue, specificity, and a soft deeper-layer teaser.",
    "session_reading": "Generate a full premium reading with a layered snapshot, a differentiated body, and a return invitation. For full/core readings, the structure should feel like: snapshot (core theme, main tension, best next move), then body (opening, astrological foundation, what your palm reveals when palm is present, what the cards are saying, where these signals agree, what this is asking of you, your next move, minimal return line). Astrology must visibly matter in combined/full readings: name the actual placements, chart tensions, elemental emphasis, or identity/need dynamics that are present, and explain what they reveal about the user and the question. Do not reduce astrology to setup flavor or let it disappear behind tarot. Palm must visibly matter when it is part of the flow: name the standout signals in human terms, explain what they suggest, and why they matter to the question. Tarot must be card-led, interpretive, and connected to the question: name the cards, explain what each individual card means for this person and this question, explain each card's role in the spread, then give a separate spread-level story that synthesises the cards into one coherent movement or tension. Do not let the tarot section collapse into a list of card names or a single generic paragraph. Make the expanded tarot state materially richer than the collapsed synthesis line, and keep summary and body distinct rather than paraphrasing the same point twice. When tarot is present, the tarot_message should feel premium and substantial: usually 3 paragraphs or roughly 180-260 words, with clear movement from card one, to card tension, to spread-level story. Avoid mechanical phrasing such as 'acts as the pattern' or 'functions as the role' unless absolutely necessary. Make the prose feel authored, not assembled.",
    "tarot_preview": "Generate a tarot preview that is clearly card-led, not a generic astrology teaser. Refer to the drawn card or cards when available, name symbolic meaning, and hint at how the spread or position changes the interpretation.",
    "tarot_reading": "Generate a full tarot reading that is unmistakably tarot-specific and suitable for a chaptered product journey. Interpret the actual card or cards, explain their symbolism, reflect the spread or position logic when available, and synthesise the cards into a coherent reading with grounded guidance. Return tarot_spread_overview, tarot_card_chapters, and tarot_spread_story. tarot_spread_overview should show the spread at a glance and name the central tension. tarot_card_chapters must include one object per drawn card in draw order, with card meaning, position meaning, reversal/upright orientation, question relevance, and personal implication. tarot_spread_story should explain the movement of the spread as a whole without copying the card chapters. Make each section do a different job: overview frames the spread, card chapters deepen individual cards, story connects the pattern, and guidance gives concrete next steps. Do not repeat or paraphrase the same sentence across sections. Keep claims tied to the actual cards or spread, make guidance actionable rather than abstract, and avoid vague mystical boilerplate unless it is clearly earned by the cards. Avoid drifting into generic astrology or full-reading prose.",
    "daily_horoscope_preview": "Generate a true daily horoscope preview. Keep it clearly about today and make it fast to scan. The implied structure should be: today's headline, today's energy, best move, watch out for, plus a soft deeper-layer teaser. Make the preview feel specific, current, and immediately usable rather than generic zodiac filler. Do not use ad-copy lines like 'for a deeper dive' or 'consider a personalised reading' inside the preview content itself. Best move and watch out should each feel like a real signal, not placeholder upsell text.",
    "daily_horoscope_reading": "Generate a true full daily horoscope, not a generic astrology essay. Focus on today only. The implied structure should cover: today's theme, today's energy, best move, watch out for, people energy, work/focus, timing, and closing guidance. For the full daily reading, fill the daily_sections object with all eight sections. Each section needs a short headline and a fuller detail block that adds new material instead of repeating the headline. Detail should usually be 2-4 concrete sentences, roughly 35-70 words, and feel materially richer than the headline. Make timing concrete with language like this morning, before lunch, this afternoon, this evening, or tonight. Keep the astrology visible but translated into plain language, and do not leave people/work/timing blank. Do not write teaser-copy for a better reading inside the reading itself. Each section should tell the user something different about how today will feel, where the pressure sits, and what to do with it. Avoid one-line aphorisms; include at least one specific cue, behaviour, or decision the user can actually use today.",
    "lunar_new_year_preview": "Generate a true Lunar New Year preview, not a daily horoscope, seasonal wellness note, or generic astrology reading. Frame it as the new year-cycle the user is entering. Use the lunar_context when present: anchor the preview in the user's birth zodiac, the current lunar year animal/element, and the interaction between them. Make the preview specific about the cycle theme, the symbolic character of the year, and one important opportunity or caution to carry into the year ahead.",
    "lunar_new_year_reading": "Generate a true full Lunar New Year reading with a recognisably year-ahead frame. Avoid generic season-ahead language, vague self-help, and recycled daily horoscope copy. This is not a daily reading. Use the lunar_context when present: the user's birth zodiac should matter, the current year animal and element should matter, and the interaction between them should shape the reading. The reading should clearly cover: the cycle theme of the Lunar New Year the person is entering, the year's symbolism and why it matters for them, likely luck/opportunity areas, likely caution/friction areas, what to welcome, what to release, and how to move through the year well with clear priorities. Make the guidance concrete and include multiple distinct carry-forward points rather than one generic paragraph. If the domain context includes reading_focus bullets, treat them as anchor rails and build around them rather than ignoring them.",
    "compatibility_preview": "Generate a chemistry-focused compatibility preview with clear relational tension and curiosity.",
    "compatibility_reading": "Generate a full compatibility reading with emotional dynamics, strengths, tensions, and grounded guidance.",
    "palm_preview": "Generate a palm-led preview grounded in the observed hand features. Name at least one palm feature, line, mount, or hand-shape signal when available, interpret what it suggests, and keep the teaser focused on the user's question rather than drifting into tarot or astrology.",
    "palm_reading": "Generate a full palm-led reading grounded in the observed palm analysis. Interpret the visible lines, mounts, hand shape, and overall impression into meaning for the user's question. The current_pattern and emotional_truth fields should name distinct palm-based insights, and practical_guidance should give concrete next steps that connect back to the hand signals. Avoid generic horoscope, tarot, or vague spiritual prose.",
    "feng_shui_preview": "Generate a short Feng Shui preview focused on the most obvious energetic or practical shift in the space.",
    "feng_shui_analysis": "Generate a full Feng Shui analysis that feels like a practical consultant walked the room, saw the friction, and gave a usable plan. Use the vision_analysis and room context. The implied structure is: overview, what helps, what blocks, practical fixes, and action plan. Each section must do a different job: overview diagnoses the room, what_helps preserves existing support, what_blocks names the friction, practical_fixes gives concrete layout/object/flow changes, and action_plan orders the work. Practical fixes should include at least 4 specific actions with reasons, not vibes. Mention room purpose, user goal, compass direction, layout, pathways, focal points, clutter, light, surfaces, doors/windows, or element balance when present. Avoid generic reassurance, wealth-manifesting boilerplate, and repeated wording across sections.",
}
